Uh, today I'm flying this very plane.
First complaint: We need cute flight logs. Black is too boring, and what they call 'pink' isn't really pink, it's more like salmon red.
I've always wanted to fly.
Today my dream came true… I flew a plane today. I still can't believe it.
FlightAware data.
Saturday I plan to try again. The weather looks bad now, but it's only Monday today.
It seems that the challenges in this area have already begun to show. Due to the FAA's stance on certain drugs, I may find it difficult to obtain my medical certificate.
This is not impossible, but it will require a lot of time and a significant amount of additional work.
Although this is somewhat discouraging, it's just another problem to solve, and it currently appears that it can indeed be resolved. It will just take a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges lie ahead for me:
FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you are taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't get a medical certificate.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
If I have the chance to customize the tail number of an airplane in the future, it must be some variant of N1337_, where _ represents any available letter character.
Naturally, the sun will still rise on schedule when I'm not around, ha ha. Really disappointing.
I have to fly again. But this damn weather is just not cooperating.
